T1  - Is there a J-curve?
AU  - Rose, Andrew K.
AU  - Yellen, Janet L.
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 24
IS  - 1
SP  - 53
EP  - 68
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/07/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(89)90016-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393289900160
AB  - If the response of the value of the trade balance to movements in the real exchange rate is described by a J-curve, then a real depreciation initially worsens a balance of trade deficit, only improving it over time. This paper investigates whether a J-curve can be detected in the last twenty-five years of American data. No statistically reliable evidence of a stable J-curve is detected. The model is checked extensively to support this finding.
